# Chat Wrapped — Environment variables
#
# This app is 100% client-side. It has NO backend, makes NO network requests,
# and therefore requires NO secrets or environment variables to run or deploy.
#
# This file exists as a convention placeholder. If you ever fork Chat Wrapped
# and add an optional integration (e.g. privacy-friendly analytics), document
# the variable here and read it via Vite's `import.meta.env.VITE_*` mechanism.
# Vite only exposes variables prefixed with VITE_ to client code.
#
# Example (commented out — not used by the app today):
# VITE_ANALYTICS_ID=your-analytics-id-here
